Bookmark this: I get the feeling we haven't seen the last of concept Mercy or whatever name they may have had at the time Recall was made.
Two hero designs spawning from one unused concept for a singular character. Doesn't that sound familiar? pic.twitter.com/d6QGZP52f0
Notice the lack of the Valkyrie? At this point, the finalized Mercy was a done deal, but looks like Blizzard wasn't done with this design
...that this character isn't concept Mercy. Or more specific, as I'm speculating, a more finalized version of concept Mercy.
Remember, final Rein and Pharah were there in the shorts too, along with their unused concept selves. So Mercy being there doesn't mean...
Finally, we get to pretty much the point I made this thread. I think we just solved the mystery of one of these unknown Recall characters pic.twitter.com/2ityfb6Qnm
This guy also screams Concept!Pharah" to me. It's known that Pharah was originally designed to be a guy, so is this one of those designs? pic.twitter.com/JxDWD9k4UQ"
I thought this was another Rein concept at first, but a closer look at the 'Cinematic Roster' shows them looking rather familiar in concept pic.twitter.com/36ptVcgzau
Blizzard maybe holding onto the design? Perhaps Numbani Rein will be established as a separate character if not playable, then in lore
What's interesting is Numbani Rein's presence not just in Recall, but the Cinematic Trailer which ALSO had the finalized Reinhardt
...who piloted a giant mech suit, but it's unclear if that idea and Numbani Rein were one and the same. https:// youtu.be/kzbNZCISJVU?t= 1m14s …
At that point, the character what would become Reinhardt was going to be from Numbani. Another idea was that Rein was a little girl...
And now we get this big guy. Once the subject of speculation (he's totally Soundquake!"), Jeff Kaplan confirmed they were a Rein concept pic.twitter.com/fZWrMV9DCK"
Both just nameless concept characters who were later established in lore after appearing in the Recall short. Keep that in mind
These two first appeared in Recall and later appeared in Ana's comic, given the names of Mirembe and Kimiko. So, they DO exist in canon pic.twitter.com/4euKeTq3Ux
Time will tell, though in-universe, it doesn't make sense for Athena to be sending out a recall to herself. Speaking of in-universe...
Speaking of theories, since we've known of Athena, there has been multiple speculation on this bot being the AI in a physical body pic.twitter.com/yqVeKnvXhw
And no, despite what Youtube thumbnail clickbaiters imply, there is nothing to indicate the first dude is meant to be Liao
Then we have those who have only appeared in Recall up to now. I even checked if any of them were the guys who died in Ana's comic, but no pic.twitter.com/S7qzk0skHt
Not even sure if that's meant to be the same guy and his helmet does make me think Widowmaker, but that's probably coincidence pic.twitter.com/AQTcg14H6X
Some of them are pretty generic, like this guy, who Blizzard seemed to like enough to have him appear up until the Cinematic trailer pic.twitter.com/8l8SYTgf8S

translations by the fans in those early years were just picked up and used in official English translations for years to come
